   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/michaelmulhern/Mason_Polly_T51.pdf">In the interview, Mason describes her master, Judge Henry Boyce, and her life on
            his cotton plantation in Boyce, Louisiana. Included are her memories of northern
            soldiers in Louisiana during the Civil War, her sadness upon the assassination of
            President Lincoln, the establishment of a station for the Texas and Pacific railroad in
            the area, and her first view of an airplane.</abstract>
